    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REMOVE - RANGE CASE (Figure 4 and Figure 5 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="29">
        <title>RANGE CASE (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302304">Figure 4</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302305">Figure 5</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302304" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302304" filename="../figg13/G1302304.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Range Case - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1302305" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302305" filename="../figg13/G1302305.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Range Gears - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>It is possible to service the range case without removing the entire unit from the vehicle. Refer
                    to
                    <hotlnk document="s13023x_HL1302301.xml" xrefid="hl1302301">OPTIONAL RANGE CASE</hotlnk>
                    . If the entire transmission is to be serviced, follow the instructions given below.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When draining the transmission prior to working on it, be careful to let the unit cool down first.
                    Otherwise, hot transmission fluid could cause burns.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Once the unit is cool, drain the transmission fluid. Remove the shift tower assembly and air
                lines (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302306">Figure 6</hotlnk>) while the unit is installed in the vehicle. (It is shown
                here on a bench for illustration purposes only.)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302306" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302306" filename="../figg13/G1302306.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Shift Tower and Air Lines Removed</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Turn off and bleed the air system to prevent air lines from whipping.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove an air line from a fitting like the one shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302307">Figure 7</hotlnk>, push the bushing down with a small screwdriver or your
                fingernail and pull the tubing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302307" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302307" filename="../figg13/G1302307.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Air Line From Fitting</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the interlock plate, retainer and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302308">Figure 8</hotlnk>). Also remove the three springs and poppet balls.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302308" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302308" filename="../figg13/G1302308.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Interlock Plate, Retainer &#38; Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the air control valve and gasket, the air lines and the three interlock pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302309">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302309" filename="../figg13/G1302309.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Remove Air Control Valve &#38; Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the backup light switch and pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302310">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302310" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302310" filename="../figg13/G1302310.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Remove Backup Light Switch &#38; Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two clutch housing bolts from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302311">Figure 11</hotlnk>). Also remove all but four clutch housing-to-case bolts.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302311" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302311" filename="../figg13/G1302311.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove Clutch Housing Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a bracket or lift hook to the range section of the transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302312">Figure 12</hotlnk>). Secure with bolts which are firmly hand-tightened.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302312" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302312" filename="../figg13/G1302312.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Attach Lift Hook</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Stand the transmission on end on a work bench that contains a hole for the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302313">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302313" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302313" filename="../figg13/G1302313.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Transmission on Work Bench</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the end yoke or flange, and the speedometer gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302314">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302314" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302314" filename="../figg13/G1302314.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove End Yoke or Flange</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the range piston housing and piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302315">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Also remove the O-ring on the fork rod and the O-ring
                under the piston.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302315" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302315" filename="../figg13/G1302315.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Remove Range Piston Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft bearing retainer caps and the air regulator valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302316">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302316" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302316" filename="../figg13/G1302316.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Countershaft Bearing Retainer Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output bearing cap and shims (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302317">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302317" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302317" filename="../figg13/G1302317.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Output Bearing Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the range case bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302318">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Using pry bars in the milled slots will make case removal
                easier.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302318" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302318" filename="../figg13/G1302318.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Range Case Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a chain hoist to remove the range case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302319">Figure 19</hotlnk>). The output shaft and low range gear will remain with the
                case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302320">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302319" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302319" filename="../figg13/G1302319.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Use Chain Hoist to Remove Range Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1302320" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302320" filename="../figg13/G1302320.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Use Chain Hoist to Remove Range Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the range synchronizer and fork assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302321">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302321" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302321" filename="../figg13/G1302321.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Remove Range Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Be aware that separating the synchronizer will suddenly release the springs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302322">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302322" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302322" filename="../figg13/G1302322.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Synchronizer Releases Springs</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses to help protect your eyes against flying parts.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch drive gear and the synchronizer cup (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302323">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302323" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302323" filename="../figg13/G1302323.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Remove Clutch Drive Gear &#38; Synchronizer Cup</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift high range gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302324">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302324" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302324" filename="../figg13/G1302324.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Range Gear From The Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the valley between the countershaft teeth with the corners of the shift bar support
                bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302325">Figure 25</hotlnk>). This will provide enough clearance for countershaft
                removal.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302325" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302325" filename="../figg13/G1302325.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Align Countershaft Teeth</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Simultaneously lift both countershafts straight up to remove them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302326">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302326" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302326" filename="../figg13/G1302326.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Lift Both Countershafts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft reverse gear and rear thrust plate together (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302327">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302327" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302327" filename="../figg13/G1302327.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Mainshaft Reverse Gear &#38; Thrust Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft reverse gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302328">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302328" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302328" filename="../figg13/G1302328.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Remove Countershaft Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing retainer plates and shims (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302329">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302329" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302329" filename="../figg13/G1302329.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Countershaft Bearing Retainer Plates</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft mallet to tap the output shaft from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302330">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302330" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302330" filename="../figg13/G1302330.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Tap Out Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output shaft bearings from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302331">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302331" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302331" filename="../figg13/G1302331.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Output Shaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When pressing bearings, use a shield to protect people from possible flying parts.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">These bearings and spacers are a matched set (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302332">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302332" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302332" filename="../figg13/G1302332.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Bearings and Spacers Match</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>If it is necessary to replace any of these items, replace them as a set to help ensure proper
                        end play.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
